        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-01-23T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-01-23T18:00:00-05:00" n="702" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d702">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.633/1–2348: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ward</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-01-23T18:00:00-05:00">January 23, 1948—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. Embassy Nanking has authority evacuate American and alien employees their
                    families and effects place safety. Therefore all personnel changes for
                    evacuation purposes should be authorized by Embassy and it will keep Dept
                    informed. Urom<note n="4" xml:id="d702fn4">Your operations memorandum.</note>
                    Dec 30 re Teiichiro Tani.<note n="5" xml:id="d702fn5">Not found in Department
                        files.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
